li.blockquote:
template<class F>
  packaged_task(F&& f);

[…]

template<class F> packaged_task(F) -> packaged_task<see below>;




-?- Remarks: This deduction guide participates in overload resolution only if &F::operator() 
is well-formed when treated as an unevaluated operand. In that case, if decltype(&F::operator()) is of the 
form R(G::*)(A...) cv &opt noexceptopt for a class type G, 
then the deduced type is packaged_task<R(A...)>.


[…]

packaged_task(packaged_task&& rhs) noexcept;

